en_203422_0	Speaker Karu Jayasuriya says that President Maithripala Sirisena has informed him to reconvene Parliament on November 07 th .
en_203422_1	He was speaking in a meeting with a group of political party representatives at parliament complex this morning.
en_203422_2	Earlier, the UNP, Ilangai Tamil Arasu Kachchi, the JVP and the Sri Lanka Muslim Congress wrote to the speaker requesting to convene parliament.
en_203422_3	UNF MPs Palani Digambaram, Mano Ganeshan, Rauff Hakeem and Rishard Bathiudeen were present at the meeting.
en_203422_4	Opposition Leader, R Sampandan and JVP MPs Vijitha Herath and Nalinda Jayatissa also participated.
en_203422_5	Later, UNP General Secretary, Akila Viraj Kariyawasam said that 118 MPs were present at the meeting held today.
